Quis avus ‘ who of our ancestors ?’

The old republicans used to admit to supper the elients, who attended them from the forum. Under the emperors this laudable custom was abolished, and ‘ a little basket' of meat given to each of thern to carry home. Nero ordered a small sum of money to be distributed instead of meat, and Domitian brought back the former practice3 Suet. vi, 163 xii, 43 7. Perhaps it was subse- quently left optional, for here we find that money was again distributed. The sum was a hundred quadrantes, about 20d. sterling.
